**Amelia Heinle Luckinbill** (_[née](/wiki/N%C3%A9e "Née")_ **Amelia March
Heinle** , formerly **Weatherly** ;[1] born March 17,[2] 1973) is an
[American](/wiki/United_States "United States") [actress](/wiki/Actress
"Actress") best known for her roles in American soap operas.

## Early
life[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Amelia_Heinle&action=edit&section=1&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Early life")]

**Amelia March Heinle** was born in [Phoenix, Arizona](/wiki/Phoenix,_Arizona
"Phoenix, Arizona"), and has four younger siblings.[3] She grew up in Arizona
and moved to New Jersey with her family when she was 15 years old.[2]

##
Career[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Amelia_Heinle&action=edit&section=2&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Career")]

From 1993 to 1995 she played the role of Stephanie "Steffi" Brewster on the
soap opera _[Loving](/wiki/Loving_\(TV_series\) "Loving \(TV series\)")_. She
also played the character for two months in that show's short-lived [spin
off](/wiki/Spin-off_\(media\) "Spin-off \(media\)") _[The
City](/wiki/The_City_\(1995_TV_series\) "The City \(1995 TV series\)")_ from
November 1995 until January 1996. In 1994 she was nominated for a [Soap Opera
Digest Award](/wiki/Soap_Opera_Digest_Awards "Soap Opera Digest Awards") for
"Outstanding Female Newcomer".

Through the 1990s she appeared in many [made for TV
movies](/wiki/Television_movie "Television movie"), as well as a role in the
1999 [Steven Soderbergh](/wiki/Steven_Soderbergh "Steven Soderbergh") film,
_[The Limey](/wiki/The_Limey "The Limey")_ , as [Peter
Fonda](/wiki/Peter_Fonda "Peter Fonda")'s girlfriend. She appeared in the
music video for "I Will Buy You a New Life" by
[Everclear](/wiki/Everclear_\(band\) "Everclear \(band\)").

In 2001 she returned to the world of daytime television, this time in the role
of [Mia Saunders](/wiki/Mia_Saunders "Mia Saunders") on _[All My
Children](/wiki/All_My_Children "All My Children")_ , the heretofore unknown
half-sister of [Liza Colby](/wiki/Liza_Colby "Liza Colby") ([Marcy
Walker](/wiki/Marcy_Walker "Marcy Walker")). Although she started as a front-
burner character, her romantic pairing with [Jake
Martin](/wiki/Jake_Martin_\(All_My_Children\) "Jake Martin \(All My
Children\)") ([J. Eddie Peck](/wiki/J._Eddie_Peck "J. Eddie Peck")) didn't
work out because of the actor's exit from the show, and so Mia was limited to
being a background character. In 2004, Heinle opted not to renew her contract
with _All My Children_ and left the show.

On March 21, 2005, Heinle joined the cast of the [CBS](/wiki/CBS "CBS") [soap
opera](/wiki/Soap_opera "Soap opera") _[The Young and the
Restless](/wiki/The_Young_and_the_Restless "The Young and the Restless")_ , as
[Victoria Newman](/wiki/Victoria_Newman "Victoria Newman"), replacing the
popular [Heather Tom](/wiki/Heather_Tom "Heather Tom") in the role. She won a
[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama
Series](/wiki/Daytime_Emmy_Award_for_Outstanding_Supporting_Actress_in_a_Drama_Series
"Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series") in
2014 and again in 2015[4] for the role.

In April 2009 Heinle appeared in season 4, episode 20, of _[Ghost
Whisperer](/wiki/Ghost_Whisperer "Ghost Whisperer")_ , entitled "Stage
Fright", with husband [Thad Luckinbill](/wiki/Thad_Luckinbill "Thad
Luckinbill") and fellow daytime drama actress [Lesli Kay](/wiki/Lesli_Kay
"Lesli Kay").

## Personal
life[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Amelia_Heinle&action=edit&section=3&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Personal life")]

In February 1995, she married her _[Loving](/wiki/Loving_\(TV_series\) "Loving
\(TV series\)")_ co-star and on-screen love interest, [Michael
Weatherly](/wiki/Michael_Weatherly "Michael Weatherly"), who played the role
of "Cooper Alden". On January 10, 1996, Heinle gave birth to her first child,
a son. She and Weatherly divorced in 1997.

In March 2007 she married her _Young and the Restless_ co-star, Thad
Luckinbill, notable for portraying her onscreen ex-husband, [J.T.
Hellstrom](/wiki/J.T._Hellstrom "J.T. Hellstrom"). The couple welcomed their
first child together, a son, on November 2, 2007.[5] They welcomed their
second child, a daughter, on December 17, 2009.[6][7] On March 1, 2017,
Luckinbill filed for divorce from Heinle, citing "irreconcilable
differences".[8]
